# .gitignore for market-foundry
#
# Organized by category. See P3.2 commit message for context.
# Adopted in Phase 3 environment hardening (public repo edition).

# ============================================================================
# A. Secrets and credentials (CRITICAL for public repo)
# ============================================================================

# Environment files (only .env.example variants should be tracked)
# *.env catches the root .env plus any <name>.env (e.g. deploy/envs/local.env).
# The .env.* variants below cover the named-suffix conventions that *.env
# does not match (e.g. .env.local ends in .local, not .env).
*.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.local.*
.env.development
.env.production
.env.staging

# Credential files
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
credentials
credentials.json
credentials.yml
credentials.yaml

# SSH keys
id_rsa
id_dsa
id_ed25519
id_ecdsa
*.id_rsa
known_hosts

# Cloud provider credentials
.aws/
.gcp/
.azure/

# Generic secret stores
.secrets/
secrets/
*.token
*.secret

# Netrc and similar
.netrc
.npmrc

# ============================================================================
# B. Local development artifacts
# ============================================================================

# Build outputs
bin/
build/
dist/
out/

# Coverage outputs
coverage/
*.coverprofile
*.cov
coverage.txt
coverage.html
coverage.xml

# Temporary files
tmp/
temp/
*.tmp

# Local archives / zips
zip/
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz

# Project-specific transient artifacts
trace-pack-*
references/

# ============================================================================
# C. Editor / OS metadata (per-developer, not project-relevant)
# ============================================================================

# Vim swap files
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
.*.swp

# Backup files
*~
*.bak
*.orig

# OS metadata
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Note: .vscode/ and .idea/ are NOT excluded. If owner uses them and
# wants configs versioned, they remain tracked. Override with explicit
# .vscode/settings.json or .idea/runConfigurations/ in those dirs.

# ============================================================================
# D. Runtime artifacts
# ============================================================================

# Logs
*.log
logs/

# Core dumps
core
core.*

# Go test binaries (rare but should ignore)
*.test
*.prof

# ============================================================================
# E. Tool-specific
# ============================================================================

# Rust
tools/raccoon-cli/target/
**/target/

# Go vendored deps (we use modules)
# vendor/   # uncomment if vendoring is ever used

# Node
node_modules/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ============================================================================
# G. Proto-generated Go (TEMPORARY — H-3.a only)
# ============================================================================
#
# internal/shared/contracts/**/*.pb.go
# TEMPORARY — H-3.a only. Removed in H-3.b when generated Go is tracked.
# See ADR-0018 ("Promoção para Accepted" item 4) and PROGRAM-0002.
internal/shared/contracts/**/*.pb.go

# ============================================================================
# F. Compiled service binaries at repo root
# ============================================================================
#
# `go build ./cmd/<name>/` drops a binary in the repo root by default.
# `make build` places them under bin/ instead (covered by section B),
# but these guards prevent accidental commits from direct `go build`.

/configctl
/derive
/execute
/gateway
/ingest
/store
/writer
/migrate

# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# Patterns intentionally NOT excluded:
# - .vscode/, .idea/         (per-developer choice — owner may version)
# - deploy/compose/, deploy/configs/, deploy/nats/  (these ARE tracked
#                            and represent canonical configuration)
# - go.work, go.work.sum     (Go workspace files are tracked)
# - .golangci.yml            (lint config IS tracked)
# - .github/                 (CI workflows ARE tracked)
# - .claude/                 (Claude Code config IS tracked)
#
# Patterns excluded that may seem surprising:
# - .env.example IS allowed (no negation needed; .env.example doesn't
#                            match .env directly).
